review_blob: Woohoo. I shared a bottle on the 4th with fellow beer enthusiasts. It went over with 4 of the 5 people. The fifth being someone who has never tried anything other than Bud Light. I quote them as saying "what are yall drinkin motor oil for?"  Very powerful brew. The oak was a bit overpowering but hey thats why its oak aged right? Poured dark, and you gotta love that when you swirl the glass the beer sticks to the sides.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged

review_blob: Got on tap at The Pub in Beavercreek. Tons of roasty toasty chocolate. The marshmallowy head made me think of smores. It lacked the punch I enjoy in a good stout. Its good but I doubt Ill buy another.

Bottle from a 6er. Pours fast, no overflow on the head. Its a nice white foam that clears away fast. The taste is a split of hops and malt. Its not the most powerful IPA by far but its enjoyable enough to want another. Great for sessions/chillin out. Gave me the fix I needed until a better IPA comes along.
Bottle - Didnt seem like a double. It was more of a 1 and a half. I felt like it was lacking flavor. Id say the companies deScription was right on.
bland, no aroma, watery, reminds me of an unsweetened iced tea.  I paid too much for some of this.

Hoppy, malty, decent pale ale. poured golden with a white foamy head. a nice floral aroma. started drinking at normal fridge temp which held a lot of flavor back, after it warmed a little it tasted fine.
A regional beer I get a kick out of when I travel to the area. Its pretty good not fantastic. One of those beers that will keep the party going after you ran out of the good stuff.
Hudy 14-K is your average golden beer found in convenience stores. I found mine in Cincinnati. I figured for 8 bucks a 12pk it was worth a shot.
